{"word":"ἰαχέω","slug":"ἰαχέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἰαχέω</b></el> <el>(ἰᾰχέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to cry, shout, shriek</i>, like <el>ἰάχω</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>ἰαχεῖν μέλος</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἀοιδάν</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to bewail, lament</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <i>to sound</i>, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <el>ἰᾰχή</el>\n"}]}